@startuml
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
top to bottom direction

rectangle "Release Gates" as Release {
  artifact "build.py docs"
  artifact "docs link check"
  artifact "package/install checks"
  artifact "smoke scripts"
}

rectangle "Workflow System Tests" as System {
  artifact "Qt Test + real server process"
  artifact "login + inventory workflow"
  artifact "future purchase/sales/management flows"
}

rectangle "Contract + Integration Tests" as Contract {
  artifact "HTTP contract tests"
  artifact "repository integration tests"
  artifact "temp SQLite bootstrap"
}

rectangle "Fast Local Tests" as Fast {
  artifact "GTest module/unit tests"
  artifact "Qt widget/view-model tests"
  artifact "normalization/validation rules"
}

Fast --> Contract
Contract --> System
System --> Release

note right of System
Primary UI automation choice:
Qt Test with widget object names.
No extra UI framework is required yet.
end note

note right of Release
Shipping confidence depends on all four
layers, not only the smoke scripts.
end note
@enduml
